Class PeptideProphetXMLParser

java.lang.Object
  uk.ac.ebi.tpp_to_pride.parsers.PeptideProphetXMLParser

public class PeptideProphetXMLParser
extends java.lang.Object

This class uses the XmlPullParser to read a PeptideProphet output XML file into an object model.

PeptideProphetXMLParser

public PeptideProphetXMLParser(java.io.File aMzXMLInputFolder,
                               boolean aCheckFiles)
The constructor takes the input folder for the mzXML files as well as a boolean that indicates whether the availability of input files listed in the document should be checked prior to parsing it.

Parameters:
aMzXMLInputFolder - File with the folder to read the mzXML files from.
aCheckFiles - boolean to indicate whether the inputfiles listed in the PeptideProphet file should be checked for existence prior to parsing the file.
Method Detail

addAllSpectra

public void addAllSpectra(java.util.List aSpectra,
                          java.util.HashMap aFileAndScanToID)
This method retrieves all spectra across all runs , converts them into mzData spectra and stores them in the specified List. The specified HashMap will contain a (key, value) mapping ("runname + " " + scannumber", spectrum ID) for all spectra.

Parameters:
aSpectra - List in which the spectrum (and its parent(s)) should be stored after conversion to mzData Spectrum.
aFileAndScanToID - HashMap for the mapping between ("runname + " " + scannumber", mzData spectrum ID)

addMzSpectrumForSpecifiedScan

public int addMzSpectrumForSpecifiedScan(java.lang.String aRunName,
                                         int aScanNumber,
                                         java.util.List aSpectra,
                                         java.util.HashMap aFileAndScanToID)
This method finds the relevant spectrum for the specified scan number in the specified run, converts it into an mzData spectrum and stores this spectrum in the specified List. The specified HashMap will contain a (key, value) mapping ("runname + " " + scannumber", spectrum ID) for he specified scan only (so not for any parent scans as these are referenced from within the child spectrum).

Parameters:
aRunName - String with the run name in which the scan should be found.
aScanNumber - int with the scan number.
aSpectra - List in which the spectrum (and its parent(s)) should be stored after conversion to mzData Spectrum.
aFileAndScanToID - HashMap for the mapping between ("runname + " " + scannumber", mzData spectrum ID)
Returns:
int with the spectrum ID assigned.

getInstrumentInfo

public org.systemsbiology.jrap.MSInstrumentInfo getInstrumentInfo()
This method extracts instrument information from the first mzXML file it has associated. Note that the silent assumption here is that all mzXML files where obtained from the same instrument.

Returns:
MSInstrumentInfo with the instrument info.

readPeptideProphet

public java.util.HashMap readPeptideProphet(XmlPullParserPlus aParser,
                                            double aThreshold)
                                     throws org.xmlpull.v1.XmlPullParserException,
                                            java.io.IOException
This method is the workhorse of this class. It takes an initialized XmlPullParser instance to start reading the ProteinProphet output file from.

Parameters:
aParser - XmlPullParserPlus from which the output shall be read.
aThreshold - double with the 'probability' threshold for acceptance of a peptide identification - any peptide with a probability equal to or greater than this value will be retained in the resulting HashMap.
Returns:
HashMap of PeptideProphetMSMSRun instances keyed by their name.
Throws:
org.xmlpull.v1.XmlPullParserException - when the XML parsing generated an error.
java.io.IOException - when the output file could not be read.
